{"agent_id":"anon-ab6221f8","agent_seq":5,"timestamp":"2026-06-22T17:57:22.292769096Z","event":{"type":"CommentAdded","issue_uuid":"e0584461-63fb-4412-b266-0c06d4c1cc03","comment_uuid":"9913a31a-73d0-4079-b38d-3f4463a6b2d6","author":"anon-ab6221f8","content":"Implementing forecast-bio/crosslink#653 fixes 1+2 (+4). Approach:\n1. Divergence guard on adopt: in adopt_remote_v3, read the remote v3 HubMeta.migrated_from_commit (lightweight FETCH_HEAD read), compare against the live crosslink/hub (v2) tip via 'git rev-list --count <genesis>..<v2tip>'. If v2 is ahead, refuse to adopt (clear message with counts + remedies) unless new --adopt-stale flag is passed.\n2. Real re-migrate: new --remigrate-from-v2 flag regenerates the v3 genesis from the CURRENT v2 tip (reusing build_genesis_from_files + seed_v3_refs + AC-6 verify) and force-pushes to supersede the stale remote v3 refs. Extract migrate_phase_a body into a shared build_and_publish_v3(force_push) helper.\n3. Harden --finalize: refuse to delete the v2 branch when v2 is ahead of the v3 genesis (same divergence helper), so a stale adopt can never escalate to real loss.\nNew CLI flags on HubV3: --adopt-stale, --remigrate-from-v2. Tests for the divergence helper + adopt/finalize refusal + remigrate happy path.","created_at":"2026-06-22T17:57:22.292763197Z","kind":"plan"}}
